      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "class TraditionalImageSearch:\n",
        "    \"\"\"Recherche d'images avec techniques traditionnelles\"\"\"\n",
        "\n",
        "    def __init__(self, method='histogram'):\n",
        "        self.method = method\n",
        "        self.features_db = None\n",
        "\n",
        "    def extract_color_histogram(self, images):\n",
        "        \"\"\"Extraction d'histogrammes de couleurs\"\"\"\n",
        "        features = []\n",
        "        for img in images:\n",
        "            # Histogrammes RGB (8 bins par canal)\n",
        "            hist_r = cv2.calcHist([img], [0], None, [32], [0, 256])\n",
        "            hist_g = cv2.calcHist([img], [1], None, [32], [0, 256])\n",
        "            hist_b = cv2.calcHist([img], [2], None, [32], [0, 256])\n",
        "\n",
        "            # Concatenation et normalisation\n",
        "            hist = np.concatenate([hist_r, hist_g, hist_b]).flatten()\n",
        "            hist = hist / (hist.sum() + 1e-7)\n",
        "            features.append(hist)\n",
        "        return np.array(features)\n",
        "\n",
        "    def extract_hog_features(self, images):\n",
        "        \"\"\"Extraction de features HOG\"\"\"\n",
        "        features = []\n",
        "        for img in images:\n",
        "            # Conversion en niveaux de gris\n",
        "            gray = cv2.cvtColor(img.astype(np.uint8), cv2.COLOR_RGB2GRAY)\n",
        "\n",
        "            # HOG features\n",
        "            fd = hog(gray, orientations=9, pixels_per_cell=(4, 4),\n",
        "                    cells_per_block=(2, 2), visualize=False)\n",
        "            features.append(fd)\n",
        "        return np.array(features)\n",
        "\n",
        "    def fit(self, images):\n",
        "        \"\"\"Indexer les images de la base de données\"\"\"\n",
        "        print(f\"Extraction des features ({self.method})...\")\n",
        "        start = time.time()\n",
        "\n",
        "        if self.method == 'histogram':\n",
        "            self.features_db = self.extract_color_histogram(images)\n",
        "        elif self.method == 'hog':\n",
        "            self.features_db = self.extract_hog_features(images)\n",
        "\n",
        "        print(f\"Temps d'extraction: {time.time()-start:.2f}s\")\n",
        "        print(f\"Shape des features: {self.features_db.shape}\")\n",
        "        return self\n",
        "\n",
        "    def search(self, query_images, k=10):\n",
        "        \"\"\"Rechercher les k images les plus similaires\"\"\"\n",
        "        if self.method == 'histogram':\n",
        "            query_features = self.extract_color_histogram(query_images)\n",
        "        elif self.method == 'hog':\n",
        "            query_features = self.extract_hog_features(query_images)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Calcul de similarité cosinus\n",
        "        similarities = cosine_similarity(query_features, self.features_db)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Top-k indices\n",
        "        top_k_indices = np.argsort(-similarities, axis=1)[:, :k]\n",
        "        return top_k_indices, similarities"
      ],

        "## 4. TECHNIQUES RÉCENTES (Deep Learning - Embeddings)"

      "metadata": {

      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "class DeepImageSearch:\n",
        "    \"\"\"Recherche d'images avec embeddings deep learning\"\"\"\n",
        "\n",
        "    def __init__(self, model_name='resnet50'):\n",
        "        self.model_name = model_name\n",
        "        self.model = None\n",
        "        self.features_db = None\n",
        "        self._build_model()\n",
        "\n",
        "    def _build_model(self):\n",
        "        \"\"\"Construire le modèle d'extraction de features\"\"\"\n",
        "        if self.model_name == 'resnet50':\n",
        "            base_model = ResNet50(weights='imagenet', include_top=False,\n",
        "                                 pooling='avg', input_shape=(32, 32, 3))\n",
        "            self.preprocess = resnet_preprocess\n",
        "        elif self.model_name == 'vgg16':\n",
        "            base_model = VGG16(weights='imagenet', include_top=False,\n",
        "                              pooling='avg', input_shape=(32, 32, 3))\n",
        "            self.preprocess = vgg_preprocess\n",
        "\n",
        "        self.model = base_model\n",
        "        print(f\"Modèle {self.model_name} chargé\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    def extract_features(self, images):\n",
        "        \"\"\"Extraction d'embeddings avec le modèle\"\"\"\n",
        "        # Prétraitement\n",
        "        processed = self.preprocess(images.copy())\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Extraction par batch pour économiser la mémoire\n",
        "        batch_size = 32\n",
        "        features = []\n",
        "\n",
        "        for i in range(0, len(processed), batch_size):\n",
        "            batch = processed[i:i+batch_size]\n",
        "            batch_features = self.model.predict(batch, verbose=0)\n",
        "            features.append(batch_features)\n",
        "\n",
        "        return np.vstack(features)\n",
        "\n",
        "    def fit(self, images):\n",
        "        \"\"\"Indexer les images de la base de données\"\"\"\n",
        "        print(f\"Extraction des embeddings ({self.model_name})...\")\n",
        "        start = time.time()\n",
        "\n",
        "        self.features_db = self.extract_features(images)\n",
        "\n",
        "        print(f\"Temps d'extraction: {time.time()-start:.2f}s\")\n",
        "        print(f\"Shape des embeddings: {self.features_db.shape}\")\n",
        "        return self\n",
        "\n",
        "    def search(self, query_images, k=10):\n",
        "        \"\"\"Rechercher les k images les plus similaires\"\"\"\n",
        "        query_features = self.extract_features(query_images)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Calcul de similarité cosinus\n",
        "        similarities = cosine_similarity(query_features, self.features_db)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Top-k indices\n",
        "        top_k_indices = np.argsort(-similarities, axis=1)[:, :k]\n",
        "        return top_k_indices, similarities"
      ],

        "## 5. ÉVALUATION DE LA PRÉCISION"

      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "def evaluate_precision(search_model, query_images, query_labels, db_labels, k_values=[1, 5, 10]):\n",
        "    \"\"\"Évaluer la précision de la recherche\"\"\"\n",
        "    print(f\"\\nÉvaluation de {search_model.__class__.__name__} ({getattr(search_model, 'method', getattr(search_model, 'model_name', 'unknown'))})...\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Recherche\n",
        "    start = time.time()\n",
        "    top_k_indices, _ = search_model.search(query_images, k=max(k_values))\n",
        "    search_time = time.time() - start\n",
        "\n",
        "    results = {'search_time': search_time}\n",
        "\n",
        "    for k in k_values:\n",
        "        correct = 0\n",
        "        for i, query_label in enumerate(query_labels):\n",
        "            # Vérifier si au moins une image des top-k est de la même classe\n",
        "            retrieved_labels = db_labels[top_k_indices[i, :k]]\n",
        "            if query_label in retrieved_labels:\n",
        "                correct += 1\n",
        "\n",
        "        precision = correct / len(query_labels)\n",
        "        results[f'precision@{k}'] = precision\n",
        "        print(f\"  Precision@{k}: {precision:.4f}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    print(f\"  Temps de recherche: {search_time:.4f}s ({search_time/len(query_images)*1000:.2f}ms/image)\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    return results"
      ],

        "def visualize_search_results(query_img, query_label, retrieved_imgs, retrieved_labels,\n",
        "                            similarities, title=\"Résultats de recherche\"):\n",
        "    \"\"\"Visualiser une requête et ses résultats\"\"\"\n",
